From: Nicolai Stange <nstange@suse.de>
Date: Tue, 09 Jun 2026 10:36:44 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] crypto/testmgr: disallow plain ecb() usage in fips mode
References: jsc#PED-15986,bsc#1266284
Patch-mainline: Not yet, downstream provision to maintain cert validity beyond 2030.

Plain ecb(aes) usage must be prohibited in FIPS mode. Unfortunately,
ecb() is special in that it's being used by the testmgr to test block
ciphers. Therefore, simply setting ->fips_allowed = 0 will not work.

Make the testmgr's alg_test() to explicitly check for an ecb()
registration and enter the ->fips_allowed == 0 logic then. Note that
this will cause  CRYPTO_ALG_FIPS_INTERNAL to get subsequently set from
crypto_alg_tested() on the registered algorithm instance, meaning that
ecb() may still be used internally by approved constructions, like e.g.
xts(), while prohibiting direct use as intended.

Signed-off-by: Nicolai Stange <nstange@suse.de>

---
 crypto/testmgr.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/crypto/testmgr.c
+++ b/crypto/testmgr.c
@@ -5949,6 +5949,8 @@ int alg_test(const char *driver, const c
 
 		if (i >= 0 && !alg_test_descs[i].fips_allowed)
 			goto non_fips_alg;
+		else if (!memcmp(alg, "ecb(", 4))
+			goto non_fips_alg;
 	}
 
 	rc = 0;
